'''Hockley-in-the-Hole''' was an area of [[Clerkenwell]] in central [[London]] where [[bull-baiting]] and [[bear-baiting]] and similar activities took place in the 17th century and 18th century.<ref>[http://www.british-history.ac.uk/report.asp?compid=45102 British History Online]</ref> It was roughly where the Ray Street Bridge stands today, north of the junction of [[Clerkenwell Road]] and [[Farringdon Road]].{{Citation needed|date=January 2013}}

