{{infobox music festival |name = Jarasum International Jazz Festival | logo= | image= | caption= 2014 Jarasum International Jazz Festival | founded= 2004 | location= [[Jarasum]], [[Gapyeong-gun]], [[Gyeonggi-do]], [[Republic of Korea]] | years_active= 2004-present | dates = October 3 ~ 5 | attendance= over 200,000 | genre= [[Jazz festival]] | website= [http://jarasumjazz.com/ Official Website] }}
The '''Jarasum International Jazz Festival''' ({{lang-ko|자라섬국제재즈페스티벌}}) is an annual Jazz Festival in South Korea, the festival began in 2004 with 30 teams of jazz artists from 12 countries. Well established as a significant international festival, every year, over 100,000 people visit this particularly popular festival and 95% of the attendees are actually previous visitors.<ref>[http://asiaenglish.visitkorea.or.kr/ena/SI/SI_EN_3_2_1.jsp?cid=697381 "Jarasum International Jazz Festival"], Official Site of Korea Tourism Organization.</ref> This 2014, the festival runs from October 3 (Friday) to October 5 (Sunday)at ''Jarasum'' (which means "terrapin island" in Korean) located in the center of the Korean peninsula.
Main line up for 2014 included Maceo Parker, Paquito D’Rivera and Trio Corrente, The Yellowjackets, Allan Holdsworth, Terje Rypdal & Ketil Bjørnstad, Joachim Kühn, Dominic Miller, Mathias Eick, Tord Gustavsen, Jan Lundgren, Gregoire Maret and Jazz Connection.<ref>[http://jarasumjazz.com/2010/artist/list_initial.php "Jarasum International Jazz Festival Artist"], Official Site of Jarasum International Jazz Festival.</ref> ==See also== *[[List of music festivals in South Korea]] *[[List of jazz festivals]] * [[List of Korea-related topics]]
